{"article_id":"Wphy6mYfwLMzZ3S8","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Supreme Court will hear arguments Tuesday on a trio of cases","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"asking","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"whether the Trump administration acted properly","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"when it decided to wind down the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"( DACA )","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"program - an Obama-era program","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"that allows unauthorized immigrants","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"who were brought to the the US as children","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"to live and work in the United States .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"A question looms over tomorrow ' s hearing , however :","depth":3},{"id":10,"text":"Why did the Supreme Court agree to hear these cases in the first place ?","depth":3},{"id":11,"text":"Certainly the human stakes in these cases","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"- Trump v. NAACP , McAleenan v. Vidal , and Department of Homeland Security v. Regents of the University of California -","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"are enormous .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Almost 670,000 immigrants are protected by DACA .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"Ending the program opens them up to deportation .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Families could be ripped apart ;","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"communities will be devastated .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"There really is a significant human toll here .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"But the Supreme Court typically only hears cases","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"that involve a significant legal question .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Indeed , the Court ' s own rules state","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"that it will only agree to hear a case \" for compelling reasons , \"","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"and they emphasize","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"that the Court typically only hears \" important \" questions of federal law .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"In this instance , the legal issue at the heart of the case is tiny .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Let me explain :","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"There ' s actually little doubt","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"that the Trump administration may wind down DACA","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"if it wants .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"Indeed , one of the opinions","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"now under review by the Supreme Court states outright","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"that the administration \" indisputably can end the DACA program. \"","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"The reason","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"the administration is before the justices","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"is that several lower courts held","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"that the Trump administration acted improperly","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"when it failed to adequately explain why it decided to wind down DACA .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"As a general rule , the executive branch must provide a reasoned explanation","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"when it seeks to make a policy change","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"that falls within its lawful discretion .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"The lower courts held","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"the Trump administration ' s explanation","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"of why it was ending DACA","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"inadequate","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"because the administration doesn ' t explain","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"why it thinks","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"that DACA is bad policy .","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"But here ' s the thing :","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"nothing prevents the administration from drafting a new memo","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"that adequately explains its policy reasoning .","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"The Trump administration could end DACA tomorrow .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"It just needs to complete a homework assignment first .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"And that brings us to a second mystery","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"surrounding the three DACA cases :","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"why didn ' t the Trump administration simply produce a new policy memo ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"rather than litigating these cases all the way to the Supreme Court ?","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"If their goal is to end DACA ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"they ' ve chosen a needlessly difficult path to this goal .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"The solution to this later mystery may be that ,","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"by bringing this case all the way to the Supreme Court ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"immigration skeptics could win a durable victory","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"that could last well","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"after Trump leaves office .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"The justices could potentially declare","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"that any program like DACA is illegal , and therefore beyond the power of any future president .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"That ' s what ' s potentially at stake tomorrow :","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"not just the fate of hundreds of thousands of immigrants","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"who have been in limbo","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"since Trump ended DACA in 2017 ,","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"but also the ability of a Democratic president","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"to implement liberal immigration reforms through executive action .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"DACA at the Supreme Court :","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"how this could all play out","depth":4},{"id":74,"text":"Broadly speaking , there are three ways","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"the Court could decide these cases .","depth":5},{"id":76,"text":"First , it is possible that the Court could affirm the lower court decisions ,","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"handing a narrow victory to the Dreamers .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"This outcome is unlikely ,","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"given the Court ' s Republican majority and the views","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"expressed by several members of that majority in a similar 2016 case .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"Second , the Court could hand Trump a narrow victory .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"It could say","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"that the memos","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"the Trump administration already produced","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"regarding its decision","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"to wind down DACA","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"are adequate ,","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"and thus the administration can move forward","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"without having to do any more work .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"If the Court takes this second approach ,","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Trump may even pick up a few votes from the Court ' s Democratic minority .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"Liberal Justice Elena Kagan , in particular , has been quite open about her desire","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"to mitigate the Court ' s conservatism","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"by pushing for narrow decisions .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"Finally , the Court could hand a crushing defeat to DACA beneficiaries","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"- holding","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"that the DACA program is , itself , unlawful .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"In this last scenario , the Court would not just allow DACA to be wound down under Trump","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"- it would forbid any future president from reviving it .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"To understand the lower court decisions","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"leaving DACA in place ,","depth":5},{"id":102,"text":"it ' s important to understand just how DACA functions ,","depth":5},{"id":103,"text":"and how its defenders justify it under existing law .","depth":5},{"id":104,"text":"DACA grants several benefits to a select group of immigrants ,","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"who came to the United States as children .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"When the government names someone a DACA beneficiary ,","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"it announces","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"that it will not enforce laws","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"permitting that person to be deported","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"for as long as they remain a beneficiary .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"DACA also grants certain privileges to beneficiaries , including the ability","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"to work in the United States","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"and to participate in programs like Social Security and Medicare .","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"The executive branch ' s power","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"to grant work authorizations and federal benefits","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"flow from various statutes","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"allowing the Department of Homeland Security to provide these benefits to certain immigrants .","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"But the power","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"to allow these immigrants to remain in the country","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"flows from something more basic .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"As the Obama administration explained in a 2014 memo ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"\" there are approximately 11.3 million undocumented aliens in the country , \"","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"but Congress only appropriated enough resources","depth":14},{"id":124,"text":"\" to remove fewer than 400,000 such aliens each year . \"","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"In other words , federal immigration officials can not possibly remove every undocumented immigrant in the country .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"And so they must prioritize certain immigrants","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"and deprioritize others .","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"DACA represents the Obama administration ' s decision","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"to identify certain immigrants as very low priorities for enforcement .","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"The legal term for this kind of judgment is \" prosecutorial discretion , \"","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"and it is well established","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"that the government may decide not to enforce the law against certain individuals .","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"The Obama administration ' s decision","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"not to remove certain immigrants","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"is akin to a prosecutor ' s decision","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"not to bring charges against low-level marijuana offenders ,","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"or a cop ' s decision","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"to let someone off with a warning","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"rather than writing them a speeding ticket .","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"In Heckler v. Chaney","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"( 1985 ) ,","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"moreover , the Supreme Court held","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"that the executive branch ' s decisions","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"not to bring a particular enforcement action","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"is typically non-reviewable by courts .","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"\" An agency ' s decision","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"not to prosecute or enforce , \"","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"Justice William Rehnquist wrote for the Court in Heckler ,","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"\" is a decision","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"generally committed to an agency ' s absolute discretion . \"","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"The Trump administration argues , in its brief in the DACA cases ,","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"that Heckler cuts in both directions .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"If the decision","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"not to enforce a particular law against a particular individual","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"is left up to \" an agency ' s absolute discretion , \"","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"then so too should be the decision","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"whether to retain a policy of non-enforcement .","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"This is a strong argument .","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"As mentioned above ,","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"the courts haven ' t really doubted","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"that the Trump administration could end DACA ,","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"so long as the administration properly explains its reasons","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"for doing so .","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"Heckler , however , said in a footnote","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"that an agency might not have unreviewable discretion","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"if it claims","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"that it \" lacks jurisdiction \" over a particular decision .","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"Thus ,","depth":7},{"id":169,"text":"as an appeals court explained in one of these decisions now under review by the Supreme Court ,","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"it ' s one thing for a court to respect the fact","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"that agencies are allowed to make policy decisions","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"without being second guessed by judges .","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"It ' s another \" to say","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"that an agency ' s non-discretionary belief","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"that it lacked the power","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"to enforce the law","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"was similarly ' committed to agency discretion . ' \"","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"So ,","depth":8},{"id":179,"text":"to clarify ,","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"agencies get to make policy .","depth":9},{"id":181,"text":"But courts get to decide what the law says .","depth":7},{"id":182,"text":"The lower courts have thus drawn a distinction between what happens","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"if the administration gives a policy justification for its decision","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"to wind down DACA ,","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"and what happens","depth":9},{"id":186,"text":"if the administration gives a legal justification","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"for doing so .","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"If the Trump administration produces a memo","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"listing policy reasons","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"why it wants to end DACA ,","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"that decision would be unreviewable by courts .","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"But ,","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"at least according to the lower courts ,","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"the administration has not done so with DACA .","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"Rather , the administration has largely argued","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"that it wants to end DACA","depth":13},{"id":197,"text":"because it believes","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"that DACA is illegal .","depth":14},{"id":199,"text":"As former acting Homeland Security Secretary Elaine Duke claimed in a 2017 memo","depth":13},{"id":200,"text":"announcing","depth":14},{"id":201,"text":"that DACA would be wound down ,","depth":14},{"id":202,"text":"the administration believes","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"that DACA lacks \" proper statutory authority \"","depth":14},{"id":204,"text":"and is \" unconstitutional. \"","depth":14},{"id":205,"text":"Those are legal reasons","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"to end the program ,","depth":10},{"id":207,"text":"and the lower courts have held","depth":10},{"id":208,"text":"that they are allowed to review those reasons","depth":11},{"id":209,"text":"- and to reinstate DACA","depth":12},{"id":210,"text":"if they disagree with them .","depth":12},{"id":211,"text":"The upshot is that the Supreme Court could agree with the lower courts .","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"Yet ,","depth":10},{"id":213,"text":"for reasons","depth":12},{"id":214,"text":"explained below ,","depth":12},{"id":215,"text":"such a decision is very unlikely .","depth":11},{"id":216,"text":"Even if the Supreme Court agrees with the lower courts ' distinction between legal justifications and policy justifications ,","depth":9},{"id":217,"text":"the Court ' s Republican majority is likely to agree with the administration","depth":10},{"id":218,"text":"that DACA is illegal .","depth":10},{"id":219,"text":"A more likely outcome is that the Supreme Court could simply deem the Trump administration ' s past memos","depth":11},{"id":220,"text":"explaining","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"why it wants to wind down DACA","depth":12},{"id":222,"text":"to be adequate .","depth":10},{"id":223,"text":"The Court could hold","depth":11},{"id":224,"text":"that the administration ' s decision is unreviewable","depth":12},{"id":225,"text":"even if it is rooted entirely in legal claims .","depth":12},{"id":226,"text":"Or it could rule","depth":14},{"id":227,"text":"that the administration did , in fact , offer a policy-based justification","depth":15},{"id":228,"text":"for ending DACA .","depth":15},{"id":229,"text":"A 2018 memo from then-Secretary Kirstjen Nielsen , for example , claims","depth":14},{"id":230,"text":"that DACA should be wound down","depth":15},{"id":231,"text":"because it is \" critically important for DHS to project a message","depth":16},{"id":232,"text":"that leaves no doubt regarding the clear , consistent , and transparent enforcement of the immigration laws against all classes and categories of aliens. \"","depth":16},{"id":233,"text":"Read charitably ,","depth":15},{"id":234,"text":"this sentence could be read","depth":15},{"id":235,"text":"to offer a mixture of legal justifications","depth":17},{"id":236,"text":"( the legality of DACA is uncertain )","depth":17},{"id":237,"text":"and policy justifications","depth":17},{"id":238,"text":"( we must send a harsh message to immigrants )","depth":17},{"id":239,"text":"for winding down DACA .","depth":15},{"id":240,"text":"Perhaps the Supreme Court would deem that to be enough of a policy-based explanation","depth":14},{"id":241,"text":"to allow the Trump administration to end DACA .","depth":14},{"id":242,"text":"The primary advantages of this approach would be that it would avoid the difficult question","depth":13},{"id":243,"text":"of whether DACA is itself legal ,","depth":13},{"id":244,"text":"and it could potentially appeal to liberal justices like Kagan","depth":13},{"id":245,"text":"who want to avoid the worst-case scenario for DACA beneficiaries .","depth":13},{"id":246,"text":"Allowing Trump to wind down DACA would be a horrible outcome for Dreamers in the short term ,","depth":9},{"id":247,"text":"but a narrow loss might allow a future president to revive DACA .","depth":9},{"id":248,"text":"Recall","depth":11},{"id":249,"text":"that the lower courts said","depth":12},{"id":250,"text":"that the administration ' s legal arguments against DACA may be reviewed by judges .","depth":12},{"id":251,"text":"But the mere fact","depth":12},{"id":252,"text":"that those arguments can be reviewed","depth":12},{"id":253,"text":"does not mean that the courts will disagree with them .","depth":11},{"id":254,"text":"Indeed , it is likely that a majority of the justices agree with the Trump administration","depth":10},{"id":255,"text":"that DACA is illegal .","depth":10},{"id":256,"text":"In United States v. Texas","depth":11},{"id":257,"text":"( 2016 ) ,","depth":11},{"id":258,"text":"decided shortly after Justice Antonin Scalia ' s death left the Court down a justice ,","depth":11},{"id":259,"text":"the Court split 4-4","depth":12},{"id":260,"text":"on whether President Obama ' s efforts","depth":13},{"id":261,"text":"to expand DACA","depth":14},{"id":262,"text":"and create a similar program","depth":16},{"id":263,"text":"known as DAPA","depth":17},{"id":264,"text":"( Deferred Action for Parents of Americans and Lawful Permanent Residents )","depth":17},{"id":265,"text":"were legal .","depth":15},{"id":266,"text":"The Court neither explained","depth":13},{"id":267,"text":"why the justices voted the way","depth":15},{"id":268,"text":"they did in this 2016 case ,","depth":15},{"id":269,"text":"nor disclosed","depth":15},{"id":270,"text":"how each justice voted ,","depth":15},{"id":271,"text":"but the questions at oral argument indicate","depth":13},{"id":272,"text":"that the Court likely split along party lines .","depth":13},{"id":273,"text":"The conservative case against DAPA and the DACA expansion was rooted in fears","depth":13},{"id":274,"text":"that allowing these programs to continue would have given too much unchecked discretion to President Obama .","depth":13},{"id":275,"text":"During oral arguments in Texas , for example , Chief Justice John Roberts worried","depth":13},{"id":276,"text":"that a decision","depth":15},{"id":277,"text":"upholding DAPA","depth":15},{"id":278,"text":"could permit the president to \" grant deferred removal to every ... unlawfully present alien in the United States right now \"","depth":14},{"id":279,"text":"Since Texas , moreover , the Court ' s gained a fifth Republican vote ,","depth":11},{"id":280,"text":"and its only grown more skeptical of claims","depth":12},{"id":281,"text":"that the executive branch may make big policy changes","depth":14},{"id":282,"text":"without seeking new approval from Congress","depth":14},{"id":283,"text":"( though it also seems to set this skepticism aside","depth":14},{"id":284,"text":"when the Trump administration wishes to impose harsh new policies on immigrants ) .","depth":14},{"id":285,"text":"It is very likely , in other words , that","depth":9},{"id":286,"text":"if the Supreme Court reaches the question","depth":11},{"id":287,"text":"of whether DACA is legal ,","depth":11},{"id":288,"text":"five justices will deem DACA to be illegal .","depth":10},{"id":289,"text":"That wouldn ' t just allow the Trump administration to wind down DACA ,","depth":9},{"id":290,"text":"it would mean","depth":11},{"id":291,"text":"that no future president may ever implement a similar program .","depth":11},{"id":292,"text":"A President Warren or Biden would not be able to reinstate DACA under this scenario .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":585,"left":364,"right":584,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":364,"left":302,"right":363,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":302,"left":301,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":301,"left":0,"right":300,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":1,"right":299,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":299,"left":2,"right":298,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":295,"right":297,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":294,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":294,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":296,"right":8,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":296,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":363,"left":10,"right":362,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":362,"left":316,"right":361,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":316,"left":309,"right":315,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":309,"left":304,"right":308,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":304,"left":303,"right":13,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":303,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":308,"left":14,"right":307,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":307,"left":306,"right":18,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":15,"right":305,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":305,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":315,"left":314,"right":25,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":314,"left":310,"right":313,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":310,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":313,"left":311,"right":312,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":311,"left":21,"right":22,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":312,"left":23,"right":24,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":361,"left":342,"right":360,"relation":"joint","nucl